Clinton Tells Libya to End `Unacceptable Bloodshed' as Protests Increase

-- B y   D a v i d   L e r m a n   a n d   K e v i n   C o s t e l l o e
-- 
2011-02-21T22:14:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/clinton-tells-libya-to-end-unacceptable-bloodshed-as-protests-increase.html
U.S. Secretatry of State Hillary
Clinton said today that “the world is watching the situation in  Libya  with alarm.”  “We join the international community in strongly
condemning the violence in Libya,” Clinton said in a statement
sent by e-mail. “The government of Libya has a responsibility
to respect the universal rights of the people, including the
right to free expression and assembly. Now is the time to stop
this unacceptable bloodshed. We are working urgently with
friends and partners around the world to convey this message to
the Libyan government.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Lerman in Washington at 
 dlerman1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  